# Micro-Demo: Pitch Deck

## Skills

Read and follow `~/.agents/skills/html-deck/SKILL.md`.

## Procedure

1. Determine demo context: which vertical, which app was built, key metrics
2. Create 8–10 HTML slides:
   - Cover slide with branding and vertical name
   - Problem statement (industry pain points)
   - Solution overview (what Domo delivers)
   - Architecture / data flow diagram (star schema → ETL → App Studio)
   - Dashboard showcase (reference the App Studio app URL/screenshots)
   - ROI / value metrics (industry-specific KPIs)
   - Implementation timeline
   - Closing CTA
3. Run Puppeteer converter to produce retina-quality PDF

## Template Reference

Use `/Users/cassidy.hilton/Cursor Projects/CobraML/Sample Assets/Template.pdf` as the baseline skeleton if available.

## Output Contract

Report: PDF file path, slide count.

## Key Rules

- Slides must reference the actual demo assets built in prior micro-demos (app URLs, dataset names, etc.)
- If no prior demo context exists, use the demo pack's industry framing for generic slides
- Match the deck's color palette to the App Studio theme used
